From: Dario Lombardo <lomato@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2020 14:42:03 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] xcsl: fix an off-by-one in premature exit.

Bug: 16695
Change-Id: I2e8548bdfaea64362d2341968a97143937e797ce
Reviewed-on: https://code.wireshark.org/review/37857
Petri-Dish: Dario Lombardo <lomato@gmail.com>
Tested-by: Petri Dish Buildbot
Reviewed-by: Anders Broman <a.broman58@gmail.com>
---
 epan/dissectors/packet-xcsl.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/epan/dissectors/packet-xcsl.c b/epan/dissectors/packet-xcsl.c
index 923919f0d61..cd0e5d698a7 100644
--- a/epan/dissectors/packet-xcsl.c
+++ b/epan/dissectors/packet-xcsl.c
@@ -109,7 +109,7 @@ static gboolean get_next_item(tvbuff_t *tvb, gint offset, gint maxlen, guint8 *s
         if (ch == ';' || ch == '\r' || ch == '\n')
             break;
         /* Array protect */
-        if (idx==MAXLEN) {
+        if (idx == MAXLEN - 1) {
             *next_offset = offset + idx;
             *len = idx;
             return FALSE;
